Preheat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, deseed, and cut
@long green peppers{2} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice
@yellow onions{2}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp},
@hot sauce{1%tsp}, 2 TBSP water, and a pinch of @salt{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a large
#ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{20%oz},
@southwest spice blend{2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up
meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove
from heat; transfer to a large #bowl{}.

Heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat.
Add green peppers and onions. Cook, stirring, until softened,
~{3-6%minutes}.

Stir cooked beef, @tomato paste{6%tbsp}, @beef stock concentrate{2},
@jasmine rice{1%cup}, and 2 cups water into pan with veggies. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Uncover and remove from heat.

Evenly sprinkle @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup} over beef and rice mixture.
Broil until melted, about ~{1%minute}.

Divide finished beef and rice mixture between #plates{}. Drizzle with hot
sauce crema. Serve with remaining @hot sauce{1%tsp} on the side.

> This fresh, hearty one-pan meal has enough flavor to stand up to the
> coldest winter days - a reward of bite after bite of deliciousness.